Welcome to AstroCraft, a modpack all about spacetravel and futuristic advancements.

Before you start playing this awesome pack, you must choose a packmode. 
There are 3 modes:

- Kitchen-Sink Mode
- (Ab)normal
- Genius
§r
§l§
§r§l§r§l*** Kitchen-Sink Mode ***
§r
---

§l*** (Ab)normal ***
§r
If you are new to modded minecraft or like a more casual gameplay this mode is for you.

§l*** Genius ***
§r
When you have played all available modpacks out there and know about the content of every mod, you can now forget about all that and experience the new mechanics in this modpack. 
This mode requires you to think outside of the box. Not only are a lot of recipes changed, machines from all mods have been integraded

All gamestages are unlocked at the start of the game. This means all items are available to you at the very start of the game. All quests are unlocked in case you ever get stuck.

If you wish to play this mode, be aware that it breaks the pack's intended progression line.

The crucible can be used to extract oxygen from Oxygenated Crystal Shards.

-Place a crucible and put Oxygenated Crystal Shards in the crucible. That will decompose the oxygen.

TIP: If you are overproducing oxygen you could use barrels to temporarily store it.
Only one profession at the time. All Quests and Planets must be visited.
Find these two items in one of the cabinets. You will need this to transfer the oxygen in the crucible to the Oxygen Pad.

Wood tools aren't strong enough to do the job. Yet blocks made out of stone pebbles aren't strong either. Therefore we need to melt such a block and make the block whole. 

- Fill the down side of the furnace with fuel.
- Put a block of cobblestone in the top side.
- Wait until the cobblestone transformed into stone.
You will be granted more researchpoints at the start of the game. Along with that the questbook is also available to you. That will guide you through the proces of this heavily modified modpack.

We need to strip the burned bark to get Oak Log
So let's strip them bitc*es!


- Take your axe in your hand
Things can get rough now!
- Hit the Charcoal Log with right click

The rock grinder removes most rock around ore blocks. What's left is an ore chunk. That ore chunk will eventually become a nugget. Nuggets are the foundation to craft basic tools and machines.

- Craft a Rock Grinder

Using the previously crafted Rock Grinder you can finally grind some ores. Low tier ores like iron, nickel, lead and aluminum can be grinded into an ore chunk. Whenever you try to smash a block of ore to pieces, there is a slight chance you won't suceed in retrieving an ore chunk. Just try again until you obtained at least the required amount.

- Gather all sorts of ore chunks
No Description

For ore chunks to be turned into something useful you need to proces them. The first piece of machinery needed is a combustion chamber. This machine is a multiblock structure, in other words block placement is very important. To help you this modpack comes with included schematics for you to use.

- Build a combustion chamber

§lSchematica Intructions:
§r
Press "+" to load a schematic. From this list you need to choose you desired schematic. For this instance you need to select "Combustion Chamber".

When you click done the preview of the schematic is placed right in front of you. If you want the structure to be somewhere else press "=". This will open another menu. 
To move the preview use the plus and minus buttons to move it over a certain axis. If you want the structure to be automatically build toggle the button "Printer" to on. This option will consume the items in your hand and build the schematic accordingly.
When you are done building and want the preview to disappear click the button "Unload".
No Description

Breathing vacuum or oxygen, which one do you prefer?
I personally prefer breathing vacuum but sadly my body can't handle that.
Since there isn't any other alternative get ready to make oxygen!

- Gather 18 oxygen shards

Once you have converted a charcoal log to oak log, left-click the log once again while sneaking. 
The log will now break down into Oxygenated Crystal Shards.
No Description

We are going to need cobblestone, probably lots of it

- Break asteroid stone to obtain pebbles
- Craft 10 cobblestone by filling all crafting slots
PS. keep a few or more than a few pebbles you'll need them later on

Gather silkworms from dirt. After you retreive or at least tried to catch a silkworm the dirt isn't fertilised anymore and changes in coarse dirt.

- Use a shovel on a normal dirt block while sneaking
- Collect at least 1 silkworm

Let's make life easier by using tools

-JEI will always be your friend

Starting a fire with pebbles and cobblestone is a bit of pain in the ass, don't you think?

- Craft a furnace

Before we're able to make a furnace, a charcoal pit has to be made.
Obtaining charcoal for the furnace crafting recipe is done by crafting log piles

- Craft a log pile (@Charcoal Pit)
- Craft 1 block of cobblestone
- Collect multiple pebbles

Stripper tools ...

- Craft an axe

We need to create a charcoal pit for charcoal.

- Place down a log pile, make sure it is fully touched by non-flammable blocks but leave the top side open.
- Now you need to slab down an adjoining block of cobblestone. 
- In order to start a fire throw pebbles to the block of cobblestone and observe.
- Once a single log pile burns all adjecent log piles will also start buring.


NOTE: Be sure that every side including the top is covered once the fire is lit otherwise all piles will just burn up instead of giving coal.

TIP: You can transform multiple blocks of log piles at once by placing multiple adjecent log piles. Then cover all log piles with a block of cobblestone on the top except for the one that needs to be lit by pebbles.

Choose which hammer you would like to make, wood or stone?

- Craft a wooden hammer or stone hammer

Gravel is cobblestone that has been hammered

- Hammer blocks of cobblestone
- Collect 4 gravel

Making planks is a bit unusual in this pack.

-First create normal oak planks by using the axe to chop down an oak log. This should return 2 planks of oak.

Now make slabs:
- Smack down a block of planks
- Break it with a hammer

Barrels will make you dirt in the early game stages

- Craft a wooden barrel

Who knew ash could be that fertile.

- Gather 25 pieces of ash

With the ash from the charcoal pit you can make dirt

- Fill up the wooden barrel with ash which you gathered before in the quest 'Charcoal Pit'
- Let it compost
- Wait...
- Wait some more...
- Retreive your compost


- Collect 10 pieces of dirt

Silkworms compost into wool which drops a single piece of string

- Fill a wooden barrel with 10 silkworms
- Wait until it is composted
- Collect 9 wool

Boy, digging with my bare hands in space is a tough job. I wish I brought a shovel with me. Luckily there is always room to impovise.

- Craft a stone shovel

Early game items come partially from the sieves. you'll be able to gather more resources as you upgrade your mesh tier. With the basic string mesh the drops aren't all that great but know this it will get better.

- Craft a 'String Mesh'
- Place the mesh in the 'Oak Sieve'

- Collect 1 'Worm'
- Collect 1 'Seeds'
- Collect 1 'Coffee Seeds'
- Collect 4 'Copper Ore Piece'

The oxygen pad is the exact thing you need to survive in space. Slab some oxygen crystals against it and you are good to go.
Space is quite comfortable right?

- Craft a 'Oxygen Pad'
- Put 'Small Oxygen Crystal' or 'Oxygen Crystal' in the top slot of the 'Oxygen Pad'
- Stand on top of a filled 'Oxygen Pad' while your spacesuit is equipped

In order to fill your oxygen back up, copper is required for the machinery to make it all posible.

- Sieve lots 'gravel'
- Collect 'Copper Ore Pieces'
- Craft 'Copper Ore Chunks'

- Cook the 'Copper Ore Chunks' this will transform it in 'Small Copper Chunk'
- Craft a block of 'Copper Block - Purity (8%)'

The 'Small Plate Presser' Will make you some nifty items eg. plates.

- Craft a block of 'Copper Block - Purity (8%)'
- Craft a 'Small Plate Presser'
- Craft a 'Lever'

You've made the 'Small Plate Presser' however you need to go on a trip. For the presser to work you need to find a single block of obsidian. After that follow the instructions below

- Find a block of obsidian in a asteroid
- Place the 'Small Plate Presser' a block above the obsidian
- Place the block of 'Copper Block - Purity (8%)' between the obsidian and the small plate presser

- Toggle the lever and collect the copper plate
§f§1§2§0§8§9§b§d§e§k§m§r§r§rA fresh start, a fresh config. This section will guide you through the config options

In order to survive you first need create an emergency oxygen generation setup. Luckily there is enough oxygen in your tank to survive at least 30 minutes. Plenty of time to improvise something in this harsh environment.

Learn how to craft the basic machinery and materials. These items are the fundemental parts needed for lots of recipes. Not only will you discover new items, you also will unlock a few automation options to start with.
Your crashed escape pod has only four tubes of spacefood. An enormous downside of being alive is you need food to seize the day. Therefore you need to become the worlds first space farmer.
